00:47:13.540 --> 00:47:15.500
Financial aid comes
in different forms.

00:47:15.500 --> 00:47:18.760
So why does it depend on how
you get the financial aid?

00:47:18.760 --> 00:47:19.515
Yeah.

00:47:19.515 --> 00:47:21.390
AUDIENCE: Because if
you have to pay it back.

00:47:21.390 --> 00:47:23.405
JONATHAN GRUBER: If
it's a grant, then yeah,

00:47:23.405 --> 00:47:25.360
you should just take
that out of the cost.

00:47:25.360 --> 00:47:27.450
But if it's a loan, it
depends what interest

00:47:27.450 --> 00:47:28.878
rate you get the loan at.

00:47:28.878 --> 00:47:30.670
If the loan is at the
market interest rate,

00:47:30.670 --> 00:47:33.370
then it's no different.

00:47:33.370 --> 00:47:36.190
But that's a great point, which
is why college financial aid

00:47:36.190 --> 00:47:37.570
comes in two forms.

00:47:37.570 --> 00:47:40.990
Grants for very low income
people, and low interest loans

00:47:40.990 --> 00:47:42.373
for other people.

00:47:42.373 --> 00:47:44.290
Why do we give low
interest loans for college?

00:47:44.290 --> 00:47:46.180
Because of this graph.

00:47:46.180 --> 00:47:49.030
Because we're saying,
