00:48:05.780 --> 00:48:07.545
But in fact, it
makes perfect sense.

00:48:07.545 --> 00:48:08.920
By having a student
loan interest

00:48:08.920 --> 00:48:11.140
rate that's lower
than the market rate,

00:48:11.140 --> 00:48:12.790
you encourage people
to go to college,

00:48:12.790 --> 00:48:15.595
because essentially you
lower this discount rate,

00:48:15.595 --> 00:48:17.470
at least on the part
that's tuition payments.

00:48:19.380 --> 00:48:23.160
So that's actually very
exciting way to think about

00:48:23.160 --> 00:48:25.800
and a very important
part of public policy

00:48:25.800 --> 00:48:28.560
